        {
          "scid": "thig3.8:1.0.3",
          "en": "8. Somā"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.8:1.0.4",
          "en": "“Mara. That vantage-ground the sages may attain is hard To reach. With her two-finger consciousness That is no woman competent to gain!"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.8:1.0.5",
          "en": "Therī. How should the woman’s nature hinder us? Whose hearts are firmly set, who ever move With growing knowledge onward in the Path? What can that signify to one in whom Insight doth truly comprehend the Norm?"
        },
        {
          "scid": "thig3.8:1.0.6",
          "en": "On every hand the love of pleasure yields, And the thick gloom of ignorance is rent In twain. Know this, O Evil One, avaunt! Here, O Destroyer! shalt thou not prevail.”"
        }
      ],
